oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Summitville street scene
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the Jackson Store in Summitville. Men, women and children are standing outside the shops and two girls are sitting in the second-story window. Two boys are playing with a plow in the street. A man and woman are seated in a horse and buggy to the right.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Stores & shops; Plows; Carriages & coaches
